            Dr. Yuki Tanaka
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-accent-dark dark:text-emerald-400 font-semibold mb-4">Physical Therapist & Japanese Wellness Expert</p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm text-text-muted-light dark:text-text-muted-dark bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full">
              <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-base">school</span>
              PhD in Physical Therapy
            </span>
            <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm text-text-muted-light dark:text-text-muted-dark bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full">
              <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-base">work_history</span>
              15+ Years Experience
            </span>
            <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm text-text-muted-light dark:text-text-muted-dark bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full">
              <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-base">location_on</span>
              Tokyo, Japan
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <article class="space-y-8">

      <!-- Introduction -->
      <section>
        <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-text-main-light dark:text-gray-300">
          Dr. Yuki Tanaka is a licensed physical therapist and wellness researcher who has dedicated her career to bridging traditional Japanese wellness practices with modern evidence-based physical therapy. With over 15 years of clinical experience and academic research, she has helped thousands of patients—particularly seniors—improve their mobility, reduce pain, and enhance their quality of life.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Background Section -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-[1.5rem] font-medium lg:text-2xl lg:font-medium text-text-main-light dark:text-text-main-dark mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-accent-dark dark:text-emerald-400">auto_stories</span>
          Background & Education
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-main-light dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
          Born and raised in Kyoto, Japan, Dr. Tanaka grew up surrounded by traditional wellness practices. Her grandmother, a practitioner of Makko-Ho stretching, introduced her to the healing power of gentle movement at an early age.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-main-light dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
          She earned her doctorate in Physical Therapy from the University of Tokyo, where her research focused on the biomechanical benefits of traditional Japanese exercises for aging populations. Her groundbreaking thesis on the effects of Rajio Taiso (Radio Calisthenics) on joint mobility in seniors has been cited in numerous international publications.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Philosophy Section -->
      <section class="bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-900/20 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-[1.5rem] font-medium lg:text-2xl lg:font-medium text-accent-dark dark:text-emerald-400 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined">psychology</span>
          Treatment Philosophy
        </h2>
        <blockquote class="text-xl italic text-text-main-light dark:text-gray-300 border-l-4 border-accent-dark dark:border-emerald-400 pl-6">
          "The most effective exercises are often the simplest ones. Traditional Japanese wellness practices have stood the test of time because they work with the body's natural movements, not against them. My goal is to make these powerful techniques accessible to everyone, regardless of age or fitness level."
        </blockquote>
        <p class="text-right text-text-muted-light dark:text-text-muted-dark mt-4">— Dr. Yuki Tanaka</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Specializations -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-[1.5rem] font-medium lg:text-2xl lg:font-medium text-text-main-light dark:text-text-main-dark mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-accent-dark dark:text-emerald-400">workspace_premium</span>
          Areas of Expertise
        </h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-text-main-light dark:text-text-main-dark mb-2">Traditional Japanese Exercises</h3>
            <p class="text-text-muted-light dark:text-text-muted-dark">Rajio Taiso, Makko-Ho, Shinrin-Yoku, and other time-tested practices adapted for modern wellness.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-text-main-light dark:text-text-main-dark mb-2">Senior Mobility & Flexibility</h3>
            <p class="text-text-muted-light dark:text-text-muted-dark">Gentle, effective exercises designed specifically for adults over 50 to maintain independence and vitality.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-text-main-light dark:text-text-main-dark mb-2">Posture Correction</h3>
            <p class="text-text-muted-light dark:text-text-muted-dark">Evidence-based techniques to improve alignment, reduce pain, and prevent age-related postural changes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-xl p-5 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-text-main-light dark:text-text-main-dark mb-2">Breathing & Relaxation</h3>
            <p class="text-text-muted-light dark:text-text-muted-dark">Hara breathing and other Japanese respiratory techniques for stress reduction and improved wellbeing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Credentials -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-[1.5rem] font-medium lg:text-2xl lg:font-medium text-text-main-light dark:text-text-main-dark mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-accent-dark dark:text-emerald-400">verified</span>
          Credentials & Certifications
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-lg text-text-main-light dark:text-gray-300">
            <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-accent-dark dark:text-emerald-400 mt-1">check_circle</span>
            PhD in Physical Therapy, University of Tokyo
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-lg text-text-main-light dark:text-gray-300">
            <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-accent-dark dark:text-emerald-400 mt-1">check_circle</span>
            Licensed Physical Therapist (Japan & International)
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-lg text-text-main-light dark:text-gray-300">
            <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-accent-dark dark:text-emerald-400 mt-1">check_circle</span>
            Certified Rajio Taiso Instructor, NHK Japan
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-lg text-text-main-light dark:text-gray-300">
            <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-accent-dark dark:text-emerald-400 mt-1">check_circle</span>
            Member, Japanese Physical Therapy Association
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-lg text-text-main-light dark:text-gray-300">
            <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-accent-dark dark:text-emerald-400 mt-1">check_circle</span>
            Certified Gerontological Specialist
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Mission -->
      <section class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-[1.5rem] font-medium lg:text-2xl lg:font-medium text-text-main-light dark:text-text-main-dark mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-accent-dark dark:text-emerald-400">favorite</span>
          Mission at Simple Senior Fitness
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-main-light dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
          At Simple Senior Fitness, Dr. Tanaka's mission is to share the wisdom of traditional Japanese wellness practices with a global audience. She believes that everyone deserves access to simple, effective exercises that can transform their health—regardless of their current fitness level or physical limitations.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-main-light dark:text-gray-300">
          Through carefully crafted articles, video guides, and exercise programs, she aims to empower seniors to take control of their physical wellbeing and enjoy an active, independent lifestyle well into their later years.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <section class="text-center py-8">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-[1.5rem] font-medium lg:text-2xl lg:font-medium text-text-main-light dark:text-text-main-dark mb-4">
          Ready to Get Started?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-text-muted-light dark:text-text-muted-dark mb-6">
          Explore Dr. Tanaka's articles and discover traditional Japanese exercises that can improve your mobility, reduce pain, and enhance your quality of life.
        </p>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-accent-dark hover:bg-emerald-800 text-white font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg text-base transition-all shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transform hover:-translate-y-0.5">
          Explore Articles
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-sm">arrow_forward</span>
        </a>
      </section>

    </article>
  </main>
